    <item>
      <title>Domain Name Impact On Google Ranking</title>
      <link>http://dollarjames.com/domain-name-impact-on-google-ranking</link>
      <comments>http://dollarjames.com/domain-name-impact-on-google-ranking#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sun, 14 Dec 2008 00:46:22 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>James</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[General]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Miscellaneous]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[domain name]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[google ranking]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[seo]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://dollarjames.com/?p=114</guid>
      <description>The purpose of this article is to report on my Dollar James blog about my analysis on whether a domain name can influence or not your ranking in Google search engine. I am not too sure whether I will be able to conclude on something reliable or not, but I will give it a go, [...]&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;SHARETHIS.addEntry({ title: "Domain Name Impact On Google Ranking", url: "http://dollarjames.com/domain-name-impact-on-google-ranking" });&lt;/script&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/dollar-james-/Dollar_James_-Domain_Name_Impact_On_Google_Ranking.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">The purpose of this article is to report on my Dollar James blog about my analysis on whether a <strong>domain name</strong> can influence or not your ranking in Google search engine. I am not too sure whether I will be able to conclude on something reliable or not, but I will give it a go, as I know there has been a tough debate about this domain name issue for several years. So how did all this happen? And how will I proceed?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">After creating my blog <a title="Logic Instrument Crash Guide" href="http://logicinstrument.com" target="_blank">Logicinstrument.com</a>, I saw that my new blog was quickly well ranked under Google as I was already on the first page after only 3 days for the Google search &#8220;Logic Instrument&#8221;. If you search for these terms under Google.com you will see that there are over 14 million results. What is quite extraodinary is that a few days after my blog creation, my blog is already ranked in TOP 10 of Google for the term Logic Instrument. So maybe the domain name has a big impact on my ranking? Thats what I first thought when I saw this. Meanwhile after searching a bit, I found under the Google adword keyword tool that there were only about 3,000 searches per month worldwide for these terms. Therefore this probably means that in terms of <strong>SEO</strong> there is little competition. But I am unable to check this. As a consequence I decided to create several other blogs, with good domain names and which have larger seaches per month.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The blogs that I have created are: <a title="PDA Handhelds Guide" href="http://www.pda-handhelds.com" target="_blank">pda-handhelds.com</a>, <a title="Eyes Surgery Guide" href="http://www.eyes-surgery.com" target="_blank">eyes-surgery.com</a> and <a title="Handhelds Computers Guide" href="http://www.handheldscomputers.com" target="_blank">handheldscomputers.com</a> ! I chose topics that i knew well, handhelds &amp; pda and eye surgery. As you may have noticed I have two domain names with a &#8216;-&#8217; in between two words, and one without. This is basically to see if this has an impact or not on your ranking. As from what I read online, it appears that in some cases Google considers that if you have the words.com domain name (ex: <a title="Logic Instrument Crash Guide" href="http://logicinstrument.com" target="_blank">logicinstrument.com</a> or <a title="Handhelds Computers Guide" href="http://www.handheldscomputers.com" target="_blank">handheldscomputers.com</a>), they will consider it as the website where the concept or word comes from. In other words its as if you were the brand, or that you owned the word. But I cannot validate this yet. This is why I created these domaines, in order to see if the domain name had an impact on the SEO and on your <strong>Google ranking</strong>. I will keep you updated with my analysis after a few days or weeks.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><p>Technorati Tags: <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/Domain+name" rel="tag">Domain name</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/Google+ranking" rel="tag"> Google ranking</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/seo" rel="tag"> seo </a></p>
<p><a href="http://sharethis.com/item?&wp=2.6.3&amp;publisher=4632b4a7-f0b8-4eac-a614-e30dd088e64c&amp;title=Domain+Name+Impact+On+Google+Ranking&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fdollarjames.com%2Fdomain-name-impact-on-google-ranking">ShareThis</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://dollarjames.com/domain-name-impact-on-google-ranking/feed</wfw:commentRss>
      <enclosure url="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/dollar-james-/Dollar_James_-Domain_Name_Impact_On_Google_Ranking.mp3" length="1361196" type="audio/mpeg" />
    </item>
